  "title": "useHits hooks with react instant search and algoliasearch 5.20",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\nI am trying to implement a custom hit component using the useHits hook, it requires me to install the package \n\nreact-instantsearch-hooks-web\n\nhowever when I try to install through NPM I get the following error:\n\n`\nnpm error Found: algoliasearch@5.20.3\nnpm error node_modules/algoliasearch\nnpm error   algoliasearch@\"^5.20.2\" from the root project\nnpm error\nnpm error Could not resolve dependency:\nnpm error peer algoliasearch@\">= 3.1 < 5\" from react-instantsearch-hooks-web@6.47.3\nnpm error node_modules/react-instantsearch-hooks-web\nnpm error   react-instantsearch-hooks-web@\"*\" from the root project\nnpm error\nnpm error Fix the upstream dependency conflict, or retry\nnpm error this command with --force or --legacy-peer-deps\nnpm error to accept an incorrect (and potentially broken) dependency resolution.\n`\n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\nInstall react-instantsearch and all the dependencies using the latest available on NPM\n\nTry to create a hit component\n\nlike this\n\n \nimport React from 'react';\nimport { useHits } from 'react-instantsearch-hooks-web'; \n\nconst ExerciseHits = ({hits}) => {\n\n    return (\n        <div>\n            {hits.map(hit => (\n                <h1  key={hit.objectID} hit={hit}></h1>\n              \n            ))}\n        </div>\n    );\n};\n\nexport default connectHits(ExerciseHits);\n \n\nrun npm install react-instantsearch-hooks-web\n\n### Live reproduction\n\ndont have one\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\nThe package to install and run on the most updated libs available\n\n### Package version\n\n \"algoliasearch\": \"^5.20.2\",   \"react-instantsearch\": \"^7.15.3\",\n\n### Operating system\n\n \n\n### Browser\n\n \n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [x] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
